    • Constructor Detail

      • StickinessCookie

        public StickinessCookie(java.lang.String value,
                        java.lang.String domain)
        Convenient object to store the two main attributes of a Cookie, its value and its domain. The Cookie is obtained when CreateOperation executes Channel.create(). A cookie with exactly these values obtained at consumer creation time must be included later in all subsequent operations including consumer deletion.
        Parameters:
        value - the cookie value
        domain - the cookie domain attribute
